profile_positions.description:
•	IMPORT / EXPORT - In charge of full Import Export Operations within a centralized logistics team and responsible for Drilling Services, Completion Systems, Artificial Lift, Drilling and Completion Fluids, Downstream and Upstream Chemicals Product Lines. 
•	Freight organization within Customs Union region. 
•	Coordination and management of the contracts and activities of the outsourcing companies
•	Searching of new international and local subcontractors/agents for preparing of more flexible rates for clients;
•	Assist sales staff in promoting new business, providing with customer information, rates, etc.
•	RFQ, response(quotations);
•   Assure complete billing of files in accordance with corporate KPI as well as 
     using valid company’s systems such as SAP;
•	Planning how much to spend or how to get the work done most cost-effectively;
•	Trace shipment through all transit points up to final destination and advise if any irregularities;
•	Sending of cargo’s pre-notice/pre-alert to clients and destination parties;
•	Constant communication with new contractors / clients and their support if required;
•	Control for cargos’ loading/unloading realization as well as responsible for cargos’ delivery to the point of destination in time frame;
•	Communicating regularly with Customs and brokers for organization of customs clearance formalities;
•	Keeping track of projects, timetables;
•	Working with claims and action in disputable situation;
•	Ensuring all job files are completed in accordance with QA and project requirements.
•	Due Diligence processing
•       Product Lines demobilization (local and international)
